FBIS3-36484 "drsov025_a_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS DPRK Envoy Denies Russia Joining in DPRK Nuclear Program SK0702121894 Moscow Radio Moscow in Korean 1000 GMT 7 Feb 94 SK0702121894 Moscow Radio Moscow Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Text] In an interview with a ITAR-TASS reporter on Friday [4 February], the DPRK Ambassador to Russia Son Song-pil pointed out that the allegation that Russian nuclear physics scholars participated in Pyongyang's nuclear arms development is groundless and false. Stressing that the DPRK has never implemented any military nuclear program, he said that the DPRK has limited research projects to totally peace-oriented nuclear energy development. The DPRK ambassador pointed out that Japanese press organizations have spread such a false rumor.
